seType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acini","Sebaceous glands","Ducts","Adipocytes","Myofibroblasts"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eacini\u003C/strong\u003E are the basic milk-producing units of the mammary gland. They are lined by cuboidal epithelial cells that synthesise and secrete milk components during lactation. Multiple acini cluster together to form lobules, which are surrounded by myoepithelial cells and connective tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDucts\u003C/strong\u003E transport milk from the acini but do not produce it. \u003Cstrong\u003EAdipocytes\u003C/strong\u003E provide structural support and energy storage in breast tissue but do not produce milk. \u003Cstrong\u003EMyofibroblasts\u003C/strong\u003E are found in breast stroma but are not involved in milk production. \u003Cstrong\u003ESebaceous glands\u003C/strong\u003E are not typically found in breast tissue and do not produce milk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy and lactation, the secretory epithelium of breast acini undergoes significant changes in response to hormonal stimulation, particularly prolactin and oxytocin, to enable milk production and ejection.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Breast acini are the milk-producing units of the mammary gland, lined by cuboidal epithelial cells.","Breast acini cluster together to form lobules, which are surrounded by myoepithelial cells and connective tissue.","The secretory epithelium of breast acini responds to hormonal stimulation during pregnancy and lactation."],"references":["\u0022Normal breast acinus\u0022 by Mikael H\u00e4ggstr\u00f6m is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 1.0 Unported license.","Zucca-Matthes G, Urban C, Vallejo A. Anatomy of the nipple and breast ducts. Gland Surg. 2016 Feb;5(1):32-6. doi: 10.3978/j.issn.2227-684X.2015.05.10. PMID: 26855906; PMCID: PMC4716863","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, 